Dunkin Donuts
I coded this 'Dunkin Donuts' website redesign at the beginning of my diploma. It was a great way for me to learn CSS and how to implement responsive design to a website. The website features filtering functionality and allowed me to gain experience using JavaScript objects.

The Women's Centre
The scenario for this project was to redesign a website for a non-profit organisation. This was my first time coding a website using a React front-end. The backend for this website providing custom posts was WordPress. It was interesting to learn how to use WordPress with React.

Papori Neighbourhood
This project was a group assignment, doing a group project improved my teamwork skills greatly. I enjoyed implementing so much functionality on this website, including: editing, deleting, posting, commenting, logging in and editing accounts. We learnt how to use MongoDB during this project, which I thoroughly enjoyed.
